/a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Capital Punishment</span><hr size=1> Just wondering where our Athiest brethren out there fall on this issue.. seems to me, if you don't believe in a whole Judgement Day scenario, or that anything comes after you die, you'd be much more reluctant to lop of someone's head or juice them full of electricity.  If this is all there is (i.e. this life), then how would you justify ever taking someone's life, minus this belief.  And now that I think about it, if our justice system has no basis in religion at all, isn't it incredible that it would sanction the death penalty, given that officially they don't believe in an afterlife of any kind.. it's so... final.  It brings up a lot of thoughts for me, but before I go on I'd like to hear what others have to say.<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
