<br>
Hope you don't mind me answering here (since I am agnostic... not atheist <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Personally, I do not advocate the death penealty. To me, it is an act of revenge (Like the US bombing Afganastan in the name of &quot;justice&quot;... but that's a different story <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and I, for one, feel that revenge is a natural basic human response, but it should be restrained for more &quot;advanced&quot; (if you will) human judgement. The way I look at it is this: <br>
<br>
Two kids are playing on the playground. Kid #1 shoves Kid #2. Kid #2 falls in the mud. Kid #2 gets angry and embarrassed, so she hits Kid #1. Why did Kid #2 do this? Revenge. I was hurt/embarrassed, so you will pay. <br>
<br>
I realize that murder is much worse than a playground spat, but the outcome (with the death penelty) is the same. Murderer takes away family member and is found guilty. Family feels justified when death penelty is carried out. ie... He killed my family member, now he is taken away from his. I have heard it called closure, but like I said... sounds more like revenge to me.<br>
<br>
JMO<br>
Elisabeth<br>
